      "content": "The corners were populated by a collection of desperate, low-grade thugs, their faces etched with the permanent strain of survival. You'd see groups of them, mostly young men with eyes that held too much street knowledge, leaning against dumpsters, their movements slow and predatory. They moved with a shared, unspoken understanding of the territory, a silent warning to anyone who looked like they didn't belong. These were the neighborhood's guardians, and they were dangerous ones.",
